WEBVTT

00:12.866 --> 00:17.273
and there were shepherds living out in the fields nearby, keeping watch over their flocks at night.

00:18.134 --> 00:23.904
An angel of the Lord appeared to them in the glory of the Lord, shown around them, and they were terrified.

00:24.765 --> 00:27.710
But the angel said to them, do not be afraid.

00:27.730 --> 00:32.197
I bring you good news that will cause great joy for all the people.

00:32.838 --> 00:35.963
Today in the town of David, a Savior has been born to you.

00:36.043 --> 00:38.067
He is the Messiah, the Lord.

00:38.848 --> 00:40.210
This will be assigned to you.

00:40.706 --> 00:43.930
You will find a baby wrapped in cloths and lying in a manger.

00:44.911 --> 00:57.147
Suddenly a great company of the heavenly host appeared with the angel, praising God and saying, Glory to God in the highest heaven and on earth, peace to those on whom his favor rests.

00:57.167 --> 01:06.098
When the angels had left them and gone into heaven, the shepherd said to one another, Let's go to Bethlehem to see this thing that has happened, which the Lord has told us about.

01:06.754 --> 01:11.300
So they hurried off and found Mary and Joseph and the baby who was lying in the manger.

01:11.360 --> 01:20.852
When they had seen him, they spread word concerning what had been told them about this child and all who heard it were amazed at what the shepherd said to them.

01:21.553 --> 01:25.077
But Mary treasured up all these things and pondered them in her heart.

01:25.738 --> 01:33.327
The shepherds returned glorifying and praising God for all the things they had seen and heard, which were just as they had been told.

01:33.968 --> 01:35.410
This is the word of the Lord.

01:50.082 --> 01:50.703
Good evening.

01:52.346 --> 01:54.009
And thank you, Tyler.

01:54.410 --> 01:56.594
It's really lovely to be here.

01:56.634 --> 01:59.018
It's an honour to have been asked to speak.

02:00.782 --> 02:07.774
I've really enjoyed getting to know Tyler in the last few years and visiting here when we're in Portland.

02:08.496 --> 02:11.922
And it's very special now because a year ago

02:12.002 --> 02:29.669
Nick and I are our little community of churches in the UK joined 24-7 prayer network and family and so it's just great to all be in that wonderful organization together and to have family all over the world.

02:31.452 --> 02:35.378
It's also great to have been asked to

02:35.586 --> 02:42.215
speak on angels because I've never spoken on angels before, so that's been fun preparing for that.

02:43.457 --> 03:04.146
So we're starting the season of Advent today, the time when we actually celebrate waiting, celebrate waiting for the arrival of God incarnate, God the Son who comes in the flesh, who humbles himself to come to earth as a tiny baby

03:04.610 --> 03:18.270
vulnerable, dependent, potentially completely unrecognizable as the glorious son of a glorious father who lives and reigns from on high over all the earth.

03:19.392 --> 03:21.094
We wait for the birth.

03:21.615 --> 03:22.997
We wait for Christmas.

03:23.498 --> 03:27.023
We anticipate in expectation all that's to come.

03:27.063 --> 03:34.354
And we get glimmers of light and hope as if the dawn is about to break.

03:34.754 --> 03:36.416
God is coming.

03:37.838 --> 03:38.839
He's on his way.

03:38.879 --> 03:44.146
And when he comes, heaven is going to be released onto the earth.

03:45.107 --> 03:51.475
As Mary prophesies, he's brought down rulers from their thrones, but has lifted up the humble.

03:52.036 --> 03:57.202
He's filled the hungry with good things, but has sent the rich away empty.

03:57.698 --> 04:07.212
And Zechariah's song confirms this, justice, righteousness, mercy, forgiveness, and peace are coming.

04:08.715 --> 04:18.910
In Advent, we share in and feel the longing for the end to darkness, to oppression, to imprisonment and slavery.

04:19.851 --> 04:21.554
God is coming.

04:23.010 --> 04:32.248
And angels amazingly play a crucial part in heralding this glorious news that God is coming.

04:32.288 --> 04:37.678
There are angels all over the story of Jesus' birth, especially in Luke's gospel.

04:38.560 --> 04:44.050
It's the angel Gabriel who appears to Zechariah to tell him that he's going to have a son

04:44.162 --> 04:44.843
called John.

04:44.883 --> 05:01.481
It's also Gabriel who appears to Mary to tell her that she too will have a son, only this time in and through the power of the Holy Spirit, who's going to come upon Mary so that she conceives even though she's still a virgin.

05:01.521 --> 05:13.394
And in our story that we heard today, the baby's been born to Mary and the first people, the very first people to hear about the birth

05:13.634 --> 05:39.090
In the whole world are shepherds, humble shepherds with apparently no connection to the royal family, tending their sheep in the field in the middle of the night, taking turns staying awake because this is the time when wild animals would come and steal the sheep, lions, bears, wolves, jackals.

05:39.426 --> 05:44.052
And is there there among the sheep alert to possible dangers?

05:44.693 --> 05:47.116
An amazing thing happens.

05:48.558 --> 05:49.760
An angel appears.

05:50.921 --> 05:56.088
The shepherds here first from one angel, like Zachariah and Mary.

05:56.949 --> 05:58.030
One angel appears.

05:59.212 --> 06:06.802
And what's interesting is that Luke tells us that the glory of the Lord shines around them, around the shepherds.

06:07.426 --> 06:13.312
The glory of the Lord is already in folding them just when one angel appears.

06:15.113 --> 06:21.719
The effect of the glory of God shining around them is that they fear with great fear.

06:22.340 --> 06:23.721
They're truly frightened.

06:25.403 --> 06:34.572
It seems that the manifestation of God's glory pretty much always just leads to fear, not primarily joy and worship.

06:35.232 --> 06:37.234
The worship and the joy follow

06:37.506 --> 06:43.733
once the human creatures have established that they're not being visited for some dreadful reason.

06:44.714 --> 06:52.282
But as always, even though the human creatures feel fearful in the presence of God's glory, they're reassured.

06:52.322 --> 06:56.447
The angel reassures them and says to them, don't fear.

06:57.288 --> 07:02.273
For behold, I bring you good news of great joy, which will lead to all the people.

07:02.954 --> 07:06.738
For today, a Savior has been born to you.

07:06.850 --> 07:08.292
who is Christ the Lord.

07:09.414 --> 07:11.157
They don't need to fear.

07:11.197 --> 07:22.115
The angel isn't here to judge or to punish, but to announce good news of great joy, the Savior, who is the Messiah has been born to them.

07:22.155 --> 07:33.874
And if you notice, the angel doesn't actually tell them to go and see the baby, but the instruction is implicit in the proclamation

07:33.954 --> 07:38.062
This will be the sign when you go, which you will.

07:38.102 --> 07:44.274
You'll find a baby wrapped in swaddling cloths and lying in a manger.

07:44.334 --> 07:47.520
You will go and see him.

07:49.043 --> 07:54.994
And then suddenly something else happens, something more.

07:55.618 --> 07:59.725
The word suddenly doesn't occur very often in the New Testament.

07:59.786 --> 08:08.121
It comes up again on the road to Damascus when suddenly a light from heaven flashes around Saul.

08:08.161 --> 08:11.186
And here suddenly

08:11.554 --> 08:26.688
out of nowhere a great company of the heavenly host appears with the angel praising God and saying, glory to God in the highest heaven and on earth peace to those on whom his favor rests.

08:28.070 --> 08:32.334
They weren't there and then they were there suddenly.

08:33.675 --> 08:34.496
How many of them?

08:35.637 --> 08:36.458
We don't really know.

08:36.478 --> 08:38.660
But this is a heavenly host.

08:38.700 --> 08:41.202
So how many is a heavenly host?

08:41.570 --> 08:43.472
Well, again, we don't really know.

08:43.512 --> 08:49.878
But early readers of this text imagined thousands and thousands.

08:51.140 --> 09:04.333
Probably because they had read Revelation 5, 11, then I looked and heard the voice of many angels numbering thousands upon thousands and 10,000 times 10,000.

09:04.914 --> 09:08.978
They encircled the throne and the living creatures and the elders.

09:09.538 --> 09:29.064
So if there are tens of thousands in heaven, what happens when they suddenly come to earth to announce the greatest news of all time, of all history, possibly thousands and thousands, all proclaiming, and then they're gone.

09:30.425 --> 09:31.907
Then the angels leave them.

09:32.769 --> 09:36.914
They go back into heaven and the shepherds hurry off.

09:37.442 --> 09:40.766
to find Mary, Joseph, and the baby.

09:43.470 --> 09:59.409
We might think it's strange that they come to Shepherds first, but the idea of God choosing a herder of sheep isn't alien to God's people who know the story of Moses and David.

10:00.591 --> 10:06.258
When God chooses a shepherd, a herder of sheep to do his bidding,

10:06.658 --> 10:10.122
God's people are coming into a new freedom.

10:11.784 --> 10:14.367
I love the fact that they hurry off.

10:15.269 --> 10:21.396
They don't even think about their sheep because something massive has happened.

10:23.258 --> 10:27.223
Once they've seen the little family, they spread the word themselves.

10:27.964 --> 10:29.546
They go out.

10:29.566 --> 10:36.114
The good news, they tell to all around them and everybody is amazed

10:36.834 --> 10:53.879
The shepherds then are the first witnesses to the Savior, the first proclaimers of the good news, the first evangelists, following in the steps of the angels who first announced the good news to them.

10:53.919 --> 11:00.669
And they too glorify and praise God for everything they've heard and seen.

11:00.709 --> 11:06.738
They join in with the heavenly host, glorifying and praising God.

11:07.682 --> 11:09.565
It's an amazing story.

11:10.547 --> 11:12.450
But why angels?

11:13.532 --> 11:17.779
Why are angels involved and what's their significance?

11:19.743 --> 11:33.266
Some people like to think about water angels and we don't really know in many ways and it's an interesting question but tonight I don't want to think about water angels particularly but why angels?

11:33.410 --> 11:43.405
What's the purpose of God creating and employing these beings, both in relation to himself and in relation to us?

11:44.227 --> 11:50.997
In other words, what do they tell us about God and how he's chosen to do things in his creation?

11:51.478 --> 11:53.821
And what do they tell us about us?

11:56.165 --> 12:02.194
Angels are a given in the Bible, whether we find them easy or difficult to believe in.

12:02.402 --> 12:03.263
They exist.

12:04.364 --> 12:14.194
We don't have time to go through a list of all the angels in the Bible, but let me just give you a brief summary of some of the angels referenced in the New Testament.

12:16.356 --> 12:22.743
Angels are primarily messengers, as we see in our story that we read this evening.

12:22.823 --> 12:29.650
Scott McKnight, in his translation of the New Testament, the second Testament, calls angels envoys.

12:30.530 --> 12:38.481
John the Baptist is called an angelos by Mark in Mark 1-2 when he quotes Isaiah, behold, I send a messenger.

12:39.883 --> 12:50.217
They fourth tell and they foretell the heralds of things to come and they bring word, they bring God's words from heaven to earth.

12:51.499 --> 12:59.250
If you note the shepherds say, let's go to see this thing that's happened that the Lord has told us about.

12:59.906 --> 13:03.651
So the words they speak are directly from God.

13:05.634 --> 13:13.145
They're also comforters, angels minister to Jesus after his temptations in the desert.

13:13.886 --> 13:19.253
I imagine that maybe they washed him and fed him and comforted him.

13:20.575 --> 13:25.682
Similarly in Luke 22 in the Garden of Gethsemane, Luke reports

13:25.954 --> 13:31.783
that an angel from heaven appears to Jesus to strengthen him in his anguish.

13:32.704 --> 13:44.242
And all four Gospels report that there are angels at the tomb waiting for the women to tell them that Jesus is not there, but he is risen.

13:46.245 --> 13:48.488
Children have guardian angels.

13:49.149 --> 13:52.274
The churches in Revelation have angels.

13:52.482 --> 13:58.971
And Paul says, perhaps surprisingly, in one Corinthians, that we are going to be judging angels.

14:00.433 --> 14:10.005
So angels aren't placed above human creatures in status, even though they dwell in heaven and we dwell here on earth.

14:11.667 --> 14:19.698
In Hebrews, it says, they're ministering spirits sent to serve those who will inherit salvation.

14:21.250 --> 14:31.021
So in the cosmic structures, humans are made a little lower than angels because we inhabit earth and they inhabit heaven.

14:31.802 --> 14:34.965
But it's only humans that are made in God's image.

14:36.067 --> 14:42.434
And though they're also sometimes called sons of God, they aren't made in God's image.

14:43.995 --> 14:50.002
And even though they can bring revelation from God, they can't reveal the essence of God.

14:50.338 --> 14:52.721
as only Jesus Christ can do that.

14:54.823 --> 14:57.566
And we know also that angels worship God.

14:57.626 --> 15:05.194
They're part of the created worshiping community that surrounds God for eternity.

15:06.536 --> 15:12.242
Rejoice, O heavens, with him and let all God's angels worship him.

15:12.262 --> 15:16.327
Angels dwell in heaven.

15:16.707 --> 15:19.410
They dwell in the presence of God

15:19.650 --> 15:40.069
And then they come from heaven, from the place of eternal worship of God, with messages and revelation and comfort for God's people, their messengers, their revealers, and their mediators, connectors of heaven and earth.

15:41.330 --> 15:47.176
So even though we don't know exactly what they are, we do know what they do.

15:48.237 --> 15:49.458
And we see all of this

15:49.634 --> 15:51.316
in our passage in Luke 2.

15:52.798 --> 16:00.548
The first angel appears with the message, a messenger with a cataclysmic revelation.

16:00.748 --> 16:01.789
Don't fear.

16:01.829 --> 16:13.023
For behold, I bring you good news of great joy, which will be to all the people for today a Savior has been born to you who is Christ the Lord.

16:13.844 --> 16:17.449
The long to for Savior and Messiah.

16:18.390 --> 16:18.610
Today

16:18.850 --> 16:28.445
has been born, and this revelation will be affirmed by a sign that they will find him exactly as the angels said they would.

16:29.988 --> 16:40.785
And at this announcement by the one angel as if to affirm and endorse that this is truly a cataclysmic revelation suddenly.

16:41.426 --> 16:46.194
A great company of the heavenly host, maybe thousands of angels appear.

16:46.722 --> 16:55.213
praising God and saying, glory to God in the highest heaven and on earth, peace to those on whom his favor rests.

16:56.074 --> 17:02.622
The implication being, of course, that it's the shepherds on whom his favor rests.

17:03.663 --> 17:15.378
And so we see an old story coming back to life where God just doesn't choose just one shepherd this time, but chooses a group of shepherds.

17:15.618 --> 17:16.800
to do his bidding.

17:17.781 --> 17:20.886
God's people are coming into a new freedom.

17:23.209 --> 17:32.504
So the heralds come from heaven with good news and then they go back to heaven and the shepherds believe them because they hurry off.

17:34.006 --> 17:36.610
But why angels in the first place?

17:36.970 --> 17:38.192
Why not a prophet?

17:38.713 --> 17:42.098
The prophets have played that role for the people of God.

17:42.338 --> 17:44.481
Or why not just the Holy Spirit?

17:45.002 --> 17:52.172
After all, the Holy Spirit can also speak, bringing words of revelation and comfort.

17:54.055 --> 18:10.578
The truth is that we don't really know, but the fact that God creates these in-between creatures to do what God loves to do on earth, tells us a lot about Him and it tells us a lot about us.

18:11.938 --> 18:24.295
What it says to me is that God loves to connect with His creation in ways that we're able to see and to hear and to understand.

18:25.176 --> 18:36.632
So in fact, He chooses multiple ways to send us messages and to reveal His plans, His purposes and His character to His beloved creatures.

18:38.094 --> 18:41.138
There are so many ways that God speaks

18:41.442 --> 18:49.612
through creation, through the scriptures, through each other in words of teaching, prophecy, wisdom, comfort.

18:50.833 --> 19:03.729
He speaks through feelings and sensations through touch and gaze and expression and imagination and poetry, and we could go on and on.

19:05.271 --> 19:11.058
God knows that we need each other, we need tangible forms of love,

19:11.330 --> 19:17.499
We need creaturely comforts, food and beauty and laughter and tears.

19:18.581 --> 19:21.926
We need to learn to be fully human, to be healed.

19:22.627 --> 19:28.756
And God uses other humans and the whole of his creation to help us learn that in him.

19:31.239 --> 19:38.610
God loves to send messages all the time, and he sends them all the time.

19:38.722 --> 19:47.977
through multiple mediators, revealing more and more of his beautiful self to us in ways that we can receive.

19:49.259 --> 19:58.573
And even though the perfect revelation and the ultimate mediator, Jesus Christ, the image of the invisible God has already come.

19:59.415 --> 20:06.706
And even though the Spirit is the one who makes all these revelations finally accessible to us,

20:07.394 --> 20:14.683
God still uses hundreds of different ways to come and connect heaven and earth.

20:16.385 --> 20:24.876
And in a funny way, it's not then that they're strictly necessary, but it is that they're fitting.

20:25.777 --> 20:32.466
They're fitting for who he is and fitting for who we are as his creatures.

20:33.808 --> 20:35.730
So angels are still around.

20:36.226 --> 20:41.975
I've heard many stories of people who believe they've encountered angels and I believe them.

20:42.015 --> 20:45.239
God loves to connect.

20:46.061 --> 20:48.084
Heaven touches earth.

20:50.207 --> 20:51.889
Do we need to see angels?

20:52.570 --> 20:54.974
Are we missing out if we haven't?

20:55.875 --> 20:57.778
Well, no, not really.

20:58.178 --> 21:02.404
But I see angels performing a role that other creatures don't.

21:02.785 --> 21:08.814
And so I understand why God still sends them and why people still see them.

21:09.915 --> 21:17.546
So in some ways angels are extra, but they bring something that other parts of creation don't.

21:18.908 --> 21:20.411
So what do they do?

21:22.193 --> 21:25.458
First of all, they bring messages from God.

21:25.634 --> 21:33.707
They come with very specific messages that make it really clear that these messages have come from God himself.

21:34.448 --> 21:40.337
They speak God's word to people really directly as we've seen in our story.

21:40.978 --> 21:45.205
So in other words, there isn't really any ambiguity once they've visited.

21:45.345 --> 21:50.834
There's no need for interpretation or questioning or discernment

21:50.978 --> 21:57.668
or clarification, as there often is in other ways in which God communicates through creatures.

21:59.611 --> 22:07.383
Karl Barth has a little section on angels, and he writes that angels belong to God wholly and fully.

22:08.024 --> 22:09.446
They have no autonomy.

22:09.947 --> 22:11.189
They do God's bidding.

22:11.890 --> 22:20.082
And he writes this, where an angel appears and is and speaks and works, God himself appears.

22:20.226 --> 22:23.271
and is and speaks and works.

22:25.215 --> 22:38.418
So there's some kind of direct connection between the sender of the message and the messenger that is actually closer for now than a human anointed connection.

22:38.754 --> 22:50.845
which is why the shepherds received this word as from God himself and Mary does the same, knowing that she's received a word directly from God and submits herself to it.

22:52.547 --> 22:57.231
Secondly, they give glory to God and they sing.

22:57.292 --> 23:04.018
In our passage, it doesn't actually say that the angels sang.

23:04.038 --> 23:08.402
It literally says, they said what they said.

23:08.770 --> 23:17.305
But looking at their proclamation, it isn't surprising that some Bibles translate the word say here as sing.

23:17.345 --> 23:34.354
And I wonder whether we shouldn't opt for sing rather than say, especially as quite a few Bible translations use sing in Revelation 4.8, where the four-winged creatures never stop saying or

23:34.434 --> 23:43.186
singing, holy, holy, holy is the Lord God Almighty who was and is and is to come.

23:44.307 --> 24:00.008
Similarly in Revelation 5, which we've already read this evening, we have this amazing, glorious picture of the four living creatures and the elders encircling the lamb upon the throne, the lamb who looks as though it had been slain.

24:00.048 --> 24:04.274
And they pour out their sung worship

24:04.450 --> 24:06.572
to the lamb, they sing a new song.

24:07.694 --> 24:16.123
And then this song escalates and spreads taken up by the angels who join them, thousands and thousands of them.

24:16.643 --> 24:28.697
And the singing grows and spreads and then John hears every creature in heaven and on earth and under the earth and on the sea and all that is in them joining in as well.

24:29.157 --> 24:33.522
And the text reads, says, but surely

24:33.634 --> 24:44.575
they were singing to him who sits on the throne and to the Lamb be praise and honor and glory and power forever and ever.

24:45.837 --> 24:56.818
And in our passage, Charles Wesley thought the angels were singing when he wrote, Hark, the herald angels sing, glory to the newborn King.

24:58.338 --> 25:05.266
So I think the translators of the RSV have made a good call in translating saying as singing.

25:06.688 --> 25:08.049
Let's say they sang.

25:09.090 --> 25:16.939
Let's say the shepherds followed suit and also sang their praise and glory to God on their way home.

25:18.441 --> 25:22.706
What if the angels are there to model how to worship?

25:23.202 --> 25:38.617
eternally singing a song of praise to our Creator that we join in with here and now in anticipation of what's to come, also heralding the coming of God.

25:40.879 --> 25:47.125
The gift of music and song is a powerful gift from God to humanity.

25:47.165 --> 25:52.050
There's a wonderful talk on YouTube by John Lennox

25:52.162 --> 25:55.366
called the Singing Brain, Being Fully Human.

25:55.406 --> 26:06.759
And in it, he talks about the fundamental connection between music and experiencing God, and also the healing properties of music and singing.

26:08.180 --> 26:14.067
You should listen to it if only for the joy of hearing him quoting from C.S.

26:14.187 --> 26:20.434
Lewis' the magician's nephew in his lovely, lilting Northern Irish accent.

26:20.674 --> 26:28.664
when Lewis describes the creation of the whole universe coming from Aslan's powerful singing voice.

26:30.627 --> 26:45.266
Lennox quotes Ian McGilchrist, the principle way in which humanity has felt compelled both to express a sense of and to make contact with the divine is through music.

26:46.018 --> 26:55.167
And in this it seems to me that it has succeeded so immediately and so intubitably that language is scarcely needed.

26:55.207 --> 27:02.233
And Lennox goes on to talk about the natural healing properties of singing.

27:02.253 --> 27:06.257
Singing literally brings health to our bodies.

27:06.637 --> 27:08.499
Corporate singing, especially.

27:08.519 --> 27:12.643
It releases endorphins and oxytocin.

27:13.123 --> 27:15.826
It unites us, relaxes us.

27:16.066 --> 27:18.088
calms our nervous systems.

27:19.449 --> 27:26.196
And it's amazing to me that we sing at all times and in all emotional states.

27:27.077 --> 27:30.280
We sing for joy and we sing to lament.

27:30.901 --> 27:32.062
We sing to grieve.

27:32.723 --> 27:34.024
We sing to protest.

27:34.725 --> 27:38.809
We sing for courage and we sing to celebrate.

27:39.870 --> 27:43.794
We also sing to strengthen one another.

27:45.282 --> 27:54.476
Nick and I had a talk recently with Nati, who is the director of 24-7 prayer in South Africa.

27:54.496 --> 28:11.282
And we were talking about how easily, especially African women, just break into song, in worship services and in prayer times, and just in homes, they will just sing to God together.

28:12.578 --> 28:22.167
And Nati was telling us about how much singing had been a huge part of healing the trauma of post-apartheid South Africa.

28:23.469 --> 28:25.611
But he also added something really deep.

28:25.671 --> 28:30.956
He said to us, you know, singing helps with enduring suffering.

28:32.317 --> 28:32.958
So true.

28:32.998 --> 28:35.680
Music is basic.

28:36.521 --> 28:41.586
The Bible is full of references to music and singing.

28:41.698 --> 28:46.163
The whole creation worships and glorifies God.

28:46.623 --> 28:48.526
The morning stars sing.

28:48.926 --> 28:50.768
The angels shout for joy.

28:50.808 --> 28:53.291
The trees clap their hands.

28:54.592 --> 28:58.156
So angels worship and angels sing.

28:59.938 --> 29:10.770
The glory that they give the sun in heaven, they give him here on earth with us, modeling and connecting us in worship.

29:11.074 --> 29:12.356
to our Creator.

29:13.778 --> 29:22.950
In centuries past, the idea that we were participating in angelic worship when we were singing was just accepted.

29:23.751 --> 29:32.083
People just believed that, that the angels would sing with us and also through us to the world.

29:34.326 --> 29:40.114
And finally, angels come from heaven and they go back to heaven.

29:41.346 --> 29:48.854
It helps to remember that all ancient people thought about the universe in terms of up and down.

29:48.934 --> 29:57.903
I'm not sure we think about the universe so much in those terms anymore, but we still know that the sky is up and the earth is down.

29:58.464 --> 30:08.274
But for ancient people, the universe was a hierarchy with heaven at the top and earth in the middle and Hades or Shil at the bottom.

30:08.706 --> 30:21.062
And people and creatures could traverse this cosmic landscape going up and down from God at the top, and the creatures of darkness and poor unfortunate souls at the bottom.

30:22.483 --> 30:30.994
Angels come from the top, from on high, and they visit below, and then they go back up.

30:31.970 --> 30:40.803
They don't have bodies of their own because they're spirits, but they can take bodily form to communicate with us.

30:41.605 --> 30:49.416
I'm not quite sure how that works, but I think it's important that they come down and then they go back up.

30:49.917 --> 30:51.860
I think it's telling us something.

30:54.324 --> 30:58.991
I know there's a lot of language about heaven being here, isn't there?

30:59.512 --> 31:01.074
Heaven coming to earth.

31:01.538 --> 31:05.223
Heaven touching earth, heaven even possibly invading earth.

31:06.385 --> 31:12.194
But that's not the only picture we get from the Scriptures because there's a movement the other way round.

31:13.656 --> 31:28.498
Heaven is still today another place, a different place and space, and we're going to join them to be taken up as Jesus was taken up when he descended.

31:29.538 --> 31:32.301
and the angels go back to heaven.

31:32.341 --> 31:35.905
Why does that matter?

31:35.985 --> 31:41.851
I think it matters because in one sense, this is not yet our home.

31:41.911 --> 31:46.797
Jesus said to his disciples, don't let your hearts be troubled.

31:47.197 --> 31:50.020
You believe in God, believe also in me.

31:50.060 --> 31:53.163
My father's house has many rooms.

31:53.344 --> 31:59.410
If that were not so, would I have told you that I am going there to prepare a place for you?

31:59.874 --> 32:05.001
And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come back.

32:06.283 --> 32:08.846
I will come back."

32:08.866 --> 32:20.522
So we wait in Advent to celebrate the first coming of the Son of God as a little baby, but we also have an eye on the second coming.

32:21.343 --> 32:29.874
And because Jesus came the first time as promised, we know He'll come the second time as promised.

32:30.530 --> 32:37.061
I will come back and take you to be with me that you also may be where I am.

32:38.423 --> 32:41.408
You know the way to the place where I'm going.

32:41.468 --> 32:54.489
It's only heaven as another place that makes sense of the earth as it is now with all its suffering and death and decay.

32:54.509 --> 32:57.394
We are not yet there.

32:57.826 --> 33:26.898
It's only heaven as another place, a place where the Son of God in all his glory, in his glorified and yet still scarred human body, surrounded by thousands upon thousands of worshipping angels into seeds for the earth, bringing us in him to the Father now, in anticipation of bringing us and the whole of the creation.

33:26.978 --> 33:32.625
to be with God forever that puts this world in perspective.

33:35.689 --> 33:46.603
Angels come from heaven to bring gifts for God's people, their messengers, revealers, comforters, and worshipers.

33:47.524 --> 33:52.530
They display God's heart to touch His people.

33:53.090 --> 34:01.461
Angels are part of God's panoply of gifts to humanity and of his worshiping, glorifying creation.

34:01.521 --> 34:05.266
But they don't dwell only in creation.

34:05.306 --> 34:07.669
They kind of dwell in between.

34:07.710 --> 34:13.437
They remind us that God loves to come to earth and to speak with his people.

34:13.858 --> 34:17.042
They mediate heavenly worship to us here.

34:17.250 --> 34:23.439
and they sing and make music in the heavenly realms as we sing here on earth.

34:24.921 --> 34:33.935
Angels come and they go, reminding us that one day Jesus will come back and we will follow.

34:33.995 --> 34:41.806
One day this whole heavens and earth will be transformed and renewed.

34:43.989 --> 34:47.154
So what do we do with angels?

34:49.058 --> 34:51.021
Do we need angels?

34:52.043 --> 34:53.906
Well, not really.

34:55.048 --> 35:01.859
Jesus and the spirits are enough to lead us to the Father and to reveal the Godhead to us.

35:02.760 --> 35:04.423
But do angels exist?

35:04.824 --> 35:05.144
Yes.

35:06.326 --> 35:09.171
And do they have a special place in creation?

35:09.792 --> 35:10.092
Yes.

35:11.515 --> 35:16.082
We know they're here to be part of our connection with God in heaven.

35:17.506 --> 35:44.754
And I do wonder if they're also here to model something for us, to show us how to speak out the good news that comes from God, to proclaim his wonders to the earth, to announce his coming, to teach us how to tell the good news, how to sing, how to glorify God in the heavens and on the earth.

35:46.146 --> 35:53.394
What if angels are here to help us to usher in the dawn of the coming of God?

35:53.454 --> 36:03.465
Giving glory to God isn't only because of what he does among us now, although that is a good reason to give glory to God.

36:03.505 --> 36:15.218
The people of God are called to give glory to God for what he's done, for what he does, for what he will do, and most importantly,

36:15.458 --> 36:16.820
for who he is.

36:19.043 --> 36:28.655
And what starts with the angels in our story is only for a short time and then they hand on to the shepherds.

36:28.675 --> 36:43.314
And the shepherds become the first people, the first human creatures to proclaim in the same way that the angels had proclaimed, with the same words that the angels had taught them, but they become the messengers.

36:43.458 --> 36:47.426
they become the vehicles of God on the earth.

36:50.533 --> 37:02.898
Angels exist not for their own sakes, but truly for God's sake, part of his great plan for beauty, truth and goodness to be spread abroad in the earth.

37:03.554 --> 37:17.612
And if that's true, we certainly wouldn't focus on angels or on an angel as a thing in its own right because they're only creatures like us and because they exist to point to God.

37:19.114 --> 37:28.626
We wouldn't elevate them or worship them or even perhaps dwell on them in our thinking because they're creatures just like us.

37:29.634 --> 37:35.861
we wouldn't even long to see them because they long for us to see God.

37:38.064 --> 37:59.570
But we would accept, I think, that at times and in places and for specific reasons, God might choose suddenly to send an angel or perhaps thousands and thousands of angels to us here to keep connecting

37:59.938 --> 38:05.043
what goes on in heaven to what goes on here on earth.

38:07.085 --> 38:18.957
I'm just going to finish by reading to you something by Walter Bruggeman in a little devotional for Advent that I picked up a couple of days ago on our passage.

38:21.219 --> 38:28.306
On this sixth day of Christmas, we remember that the angels showed up for work on the first no owl.

38:29.442 --> 38:37.773
God dispatched them specifically to Bethlehem and out of the way village south of Jerusalem to proclaim God's glory.

38:37.793 --> 38:47.065
They wondered about that, better to bring the message to Jerusalem or Damascus or Tyre or Nineveh, but they obeyed.

38:47.125 --> 38:54.935
Then the Holy One added to the message, declare peace on earth for all humanity.

38:54.975 --> 38:57.138
They obeyed

38:57.506 --> 39:01.071
went to Bethlehem and filled the sky with song.

39:02.393 --> 39:07.259
Glory to God in the highest and peace on earth, good will to humanity.

39:07.279 --> 39:11.385
Along with the shepherds, we hear this song.

39:12.487 --> 39:19.116
It's partly a declaration, there will be and is glory in heaven and peace on earth.

39:19.697 --> 39:26.546
But it's also a summons, a call to praise God and do peace.

39:27.970 --> 39:32.154
Do praise with your tongue, do peace with your feet.

39:33.356 --> 39:37.660
We give you thanks for such good angelic words among us.

39:38.541 --> 39:38.921
Amen.

39:44.047 --> 39:47.871
Thanks for joining the Bridgestown family as we engage in this teaching series.

39:48.592 --> 39:54.738
To learn more about the life of our church and how you can get involved, visit bridgestown.church.com.

39:55.202 --> 40:03.380
If you're interested in contributing financially to Bridgestown Church and to our ministry, you can do that at bridgestown.church.gov.

40:04.142 --> 40:13.522
Wherever you're joining us from, we hope this resource blesses you and encourages you to be with Jesus, become like Jesus, and do what Jesus did.

